  "text": "The Poisson ratio, the ratio of the transverse contracting strain to the elongation strain, of incompressible biological materials is assumed to be between 0.45 to 0.50. However, Poisson ratio was chosen to be 0.50, a common approximation used in literature for all TMPs and ex vivo animal tissues in this study [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
